<p>I am making an application based on Dropwizard .I have the following representation that's called <strong>Flight</strong>, I used <strong>annotations</strong> to validate the form related to <strong>Flight</strong> representation.</p>  <pre><code>import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonFormat; import org.mongodb.morphia.annotations.Entity; import org.mongodb.morphia.annotations.Id; import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull; import java.util.Date;  @Entity("Flight") public class Flight {     @Id     String id;     @JsonFormat(shape=JsonFormat.Shape.STRING, pattern="yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm", timezone="CET")     @NotNull     private Date departureDate;     @JsonFormat(shape=JsonFormat.Shape.STRING, pattern="yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm",  timezone="CET")     @NotNull     private Date arrivalDate;     @NotNull     private Airport arrivalAirport;     // getters and setters methods ... } </code></pre>  <p>I use @JsonFormat(shape=JsonFormat.Shape.STRING, pattern="yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm", timezone="CET") to serialize this date with this format . I succeed to display error messages when I sent form with empty fields through the @NotNull, but when I type a invalid date format and empty fields in the same form I got only </p>  <pre><code>{code: 400, message: "Unable to process JSON"}       code: 400       message: "Unable to process JSON" </code></pre>  <p><em>Is it possible to customize this error message of date validation and show the others validation messages at the same time?</em></p>  <p>For example I got <strong>"arrivalAirport: may not be null"</strong> when I didn't enter only arrivalAirport value.   I want to receive for example:</p>  <pre><code>**"departureDate: invalid date format"**  **"arrivalAirport: may not be null"** </code></pre>  <p>When I didn't enter an arrivalAirport value and an invalid format of departureDate value.</p>  <p>Thank you.</p>